{"id": "duc04-testb-45:6#20", "contents": "The State Department has been quick to close embassies temporarily if attacks seem imminent since the bombings. However, it would be interesting to know if the intelligence behind those decisions was any more credible than Ahmed's warning. The department's handling of security matters has been criticized, with a tendency to blame limited funding and bureaucratic inertia. While additional money could have made it possible to harden defenses at more embassies, more decisive leadership in the department could have assured preventive steps were taken in East Africa."}
